================================================================================
Per-skill license overrides
================================================================================

The following skills carry a different per-file license declaration in
their `SKILL.md` frontmatter. Where the per-file declaration differs
from the repository default (AGPL-3.0-or-later), the per-file license
governs that skill and its `references/` and `evals/` subdirectories.

  skills/dsql-to-analytics-pipeline/   Apache-2.0
  skills/streaming-into-data-lake/     Apache-2.0

These two skills originated as drafts intended for submission to the
public AWS Agent Toolkit (https://github.com/aws/agent-toolkit-for-aws),
which is Apache-2.0 licensed. The Apache-2.0 declaration is preserved
on the per-skill files so the upstream submission path remains
license-compatible. If you fork those subdirectories you receive them
under Apache-2.0; if you fork the rest of the repository you receive it
under AGPL-3.0-or-later.

================================================================================
Attributions
================================================================================

The skills under `skills/` describe patterns derived from a working
sample pipeline at https://github.com/jaingxyz/dsql-redshift-cdc-pipeline.
Some of the SQL idioms and CloudFormation snippets reflect choices made
in that pipeline.
